==Old English==
===Etymology===
Cognate with Old High German ''[[druoen]]''.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈðrowiɑn/}} (''poetic'' {{IPA|/ˈðro:wiɑn/}})

===Verb===
'''þrowian''' (poetic {{Latinx|'''þrōwian'''}}) (class 2 weak)

# to [[suffer]], [[endure]]
#:''ic geswincdagum earfoðhwile oft þrowade.''  I often suffered times of hardship, days of toil.  (''The Seafarer'')

